            <h3> MobiKlinic Privacy Policy</h3>
            <p>Last updated: August 13, 2023</p>
            <hr>

            <h5> 1. Collecting and Using Your Personal Data</h5>
            <p>Mobiklinic (“we,” “us,” or “our”) shares your concerns about maintaining the integrity and
                privacy of personal
                information collected on the internet. We are committed to protecting your privacy, and this privacy
                policy (“Policy”)
                is intended to describe our information collection and dissemination practices in connection with
                Mobiklinic
                websites or any mobile or service that links to or refers to
                this Policy
                (collectively, the “Sites”).

                Please review the entire Policy and feel free to contact us using the contact information below if you
                have any
                questions. By using the Sites, you consent to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information in
                accordance with
                the Policy.</p>
            <h4>2. Information we collect</h4>

            <p>While using Our applications & Sites, We may ask You to provide us with certain personally identifiable
                information
                that can
                be
                used to contact or identify You. Personally identifiable information may include, but is not limited to:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Personal Information: </strong>When you register as a Community Health Provider (CHP)
                        and use ourour sites & App, we may collect information that can be used
                        to identify you, such as your name, contact information, and Location.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Patient Information: </strong>As part of the medical services provided through our our
                        sites & App,
                        you may enter patient information including but not limited to
                        vaccination records, diagnosis details, and antenatal information.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Usage Data:</strong>We may automatically collect usage information, such as the actions
                        you perform within our sites & App, the frequency of use,
                        and the duration of your sessions.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Device Information: </strong> We may collect information about the mobile device you use
                        to access our App, including the hardware model, operating
                        system version, unique device identifiers, and mobile network information.</p>
                </li>

            </ul>

            <h4>3. How We Use Your Information</h4>
            <p>We may use your Personal Data for the following purposes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Providing and improving our medical services and App functionality.

                </li>
                <li>
                    Managing user accounts and maintaining accurate patient records.

                </li>
                <li>
                    Sending you important updates and administrative messages.

                </li>
                <li>
                    Analyzing usage patterns to enhance user experience and optimize the Sites and apps performance

                </li>
                <li>
                    Protecting our rights, safety, and security, as well as those of our users.

                </li>
            </ul>

            <h5>4. Disclosure of Your Information</h5>
            <p>We may share your information in the following ways:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>With Other Users: </strong>Your patient information may be shared with other registered
                        users within the MobiKlinic network, such as fellow community Health Providers,
                        for the purpose of providing comprehensive medical care.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>With Third-Party Service Providers: </strong>We may engage third-party service providers
                        to assist us in delivering our services, and they may have access to your
                        information solely for the purpose of performing their tasks</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><strong>Legal Requirements:</strong>We may disclose your information if required by law or if we
                        believe that such disclosure is necessary to protect our
                        rights, your safety, or the safety of others.</p>
                </li>


            </ul>

            <h5>5. Data Security</h5>
            <p>We take appropriate measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration,
                disclosure, or
                destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely
                secure, and we
                cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>

            <h5>6. Your Choices</h5>
            <p>You can control and update certain personal information by accessing your account settings within the
                App. You can also
                choose not to provide certain information, although this may limit your access to certain features of
                the App.</p>

            <h5>7. Children's Privacy</h5>
            <p>
                We do not intentionally without consent intend to collect personal information from children. Therefore,
                all information collect from
                children will have consent from parents or guardians.
            </p>

            <h5>8. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h5>
            <p>We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective upon
                posting the revised
                policy on the App. Your continued use of our Sites & App after such changes signifies your acceptance of
                the
                revised Privacy
                Policy.</p>



            <h5>9. Agreement</h5>
            <p>By using MobiKlinic, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to
                its terms and
                conditions.</p>
            <h5>10. Contact Us</h5>
            <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
                dev@mobiklinic.com.</p>
